o gift, to offer as a gift","examples":[{"text":"قَالَ فَقَالَ رَسُولُ ٱللَّهِ—صَلَّى ٱللّٰهُ عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ—: «ٱلْمُهَجِّرُ إِلَى الْجُمُعَةِ كَٱلْمُهْدِي بَدَنَةً ثُمَّ كَٱلْمُهْدِي بَقَرَةً ثُمَّ كَٱلْمُهْدِي شَاةً ثُمَّ كَٱلْمُهْدِي بَطَّةً ثُمَّ كَٱلْمُهْدِي دَجَاجَةً ثُمَّ كَٱلْمُهْدِي بَيْضَةً».","english":"The Messenger of Allah—peace be upon him—said: “The one who comes early to the Friday prayer is like one who sacrifices a camel, then like one who sacrifices a cow, then like one who sacrifices a sheep, then like one who sacrifices a duck, then like one who sacrifices a chicken, then like one who sacrifices an egg.”"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"better guided","examples":[{"text":"أَفَمَن يَمۡشِي مُكِبًّا عَلَىٰ وَجۡهِهِۦۤ أَهۡدَىٰۤ أَمَّن يَمۡشِي سَوِيًّا عَلَىٰ صِرَ ٰ⁠طࣲ مُّسۡتَقِيمࣲ"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"more guiding","examples":[{"text":"قُلۡ فَأۡتُوا۟ بِكِتَـٰبࣲ مِّنۡ عِندِ ٱللَّهِ هُوَ أَهۡدَىٰ مِنۡهُمَاۤ أَتَّبِعۡهُ إِن كُنتُمۡ صَـٰدِقِینَ"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"See the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":["/ʔah.daː/"],"lanes_definition":null,"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%A3%D9%87%D8%AF%D9%89/","headword_ar":"أهدى الهدية","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_50","lexicon_en":"Kâtip Çelebi / Ḥājī Khalīfa, Kashf al-Ẓunūn ʿan Asāmī al-Kutub wa-l-Funūn (d. 1657)","lexicon_ar":"كشف الظنون عن أسامي الكتب والفنون لحاجي خليفة","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=133282#813370","body_html":"أهدى الهدية<br>...."}]}}